Senate Resolution 360
By: Senators James of the 28th, Rhett of the 33rd, Jackson of the 41st, Mangham of the 55th,
Jones of the 10th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Tyler Perry; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, a visionary filmmaker, playwright, author, and entrepreneur, Tyler Perry has
3 built an entertainment empire that currently spans 24 feature films, 20 stage plays, 17
4 television series, and two New York Times bestselling books; and
5 WHEREAS, born and raised in New Orleans, Tyler Perry overcame a childhood marked by
6 poverty and adversity, transforming his experiences into compelling narratives that would
7 later shape his career and artistic legacy; and
8 WHEREAS, in 1992, he wrote and self-financed his first stage play, I Know I've Been
9 Changed, which initially struggled to find an audience but, through his perseverance and
10 dedication, became a resounding success six years later, leading to sold-out performances at
11 the Fox Theatre in Atlanta; and
12 WHEREAS, he revolutionized modern theater with 13 original plays over the next 13 years,
13 including I Can Do Bad All By Myself, which introduced the iconic Madea character, a
14 beloved figure that has since become a cultural phenomenon; and
