15 WHEREAS, in 2005, he made his directorial debut with Diary of a Mad Black Woman, a box
16 office hit that launched his film career, followed by a series of successful movies such as
17 Madea's Family Reunion, Why Did I Get Married?, and The Family That Preys; and
18 WHEREAS, in 2006, he became a bestselling author with Don't Make a Black Woman Take
19 Off Her Earrings: Madea's Uninhibited Commentaries on Life and Love, which topped the
20 New York Times bestseller list for eight consecutive weeks; and
21 WHEREAS, in 2007, he expanded into television with House of Payne, the highest-rated
22 first-run syndicated cable show of all time, followed by Meet the Browns, Love Thy
23 Neighbor, The Haves and The Have Nots, and other groundbreaking series; and
24 WHEREAS, in 2015, he acquired Fort McPherson in Atlanta to expand Tyler Perry Studios,
25 transforming the 330-acre site into one of the largest film production studios in the world,
26 creating more than 400 job opportunities and positioning Atlanta as a major hub for film and
27 television production; and
28 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
29 appropriately honored during this special time.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
31 recognize and commend Tyler Perry for his extraordinary achievements in entertainment, his
32 contributions to the cultural and economic landscape of Georgia, and his unwavering
33 commitment to storytelling that uplifts and inspires.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
35 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Tyler Perry.
